  "aiHints": {
    "analysisContext": "TAK file structure: magic(4B LE,=0x6BEA8D74, bytes: 74 8D EA 6B) + metadata_blocks. Each metadata block: type(6b) + size(varied) + data + CRC-32(3B). Block types: STREAM_INFO(type=4: contains sample rate, bit depth, frame size code, channel count, total samples), ENCODER_INFO(type=6), SEEK_TABLE(type=1), MD5(type=22), END_OF_FILE(type=0). Stream parameters in STREAM_INFO: codec(3b: 2=v2.0/3=v2.2), num_samples(35b), sample_rate(18b in Hz), bps(5b, bits per sample), channel_config(4b, channel count-1), has_extension(1b). TAK uses a bit-packing format with CRC-3 checksums on metadata blocks (not CRC-32 as incorrectly stated elsewhere — TAK uses a 3-byte hash). Common sample rates: 44100, 48000, 96000 Hz. Bit depths: 8, 16, 24 bits.",
    "suggestedInspections": [
      "Verify TAK magic: bytes 0-3 must be 74 8D EA 6B",
      "Locate STREAM_INFO block (type=4) early in file for audio parameters",
      "Extract sample_rate (18b) from STREAM_INFO for frequency",
      "Extract bps (5b) from STREAM_INFO for bit depth",
      "Extract channel_config + 1 for channel count"
    ]
  },
  "software": [
    "takc.exe (official TAK encoder/decoder by Thomas Becker)",
    "foobar2000 (with tak_deco_lib plugin)",
    "dBpoweramp (TAK codec)",
    "FFmpeg (TAK decoder)"
  ],
  "formatRelationships": {
    "category": "Audio",
    "extensions": [".tak"],
    "relatedFormats": ["FLAC", "WV", "APE"],
    "note": "TAK is a Windows-only proprietary lossless codec with better compression than FLAC and faster decoding than APE at similar compression levels. Created by Thomas Becker (handle 'Tako Schotanus'). Closed-source codec library; reverse-engineered FFmpeg decoder exists."
  },
